- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with enumeration of dominating sets, which is a problem in combinatorics and discrete mathematics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes two algorithms for solving the enumeration problems.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the proposed algorithms.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as dominating sets are used in game theory to model control and influence in a network.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as dominating sets have applications in robotics for sensor placement and coverage problems.
